<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1>
	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		<td valign=middle align=right class="header">Composing A Message</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text">To compose a new message.</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>To</strong>, <strong>Cc</strong> 
      or <strong>Bcc</strong> link to open a small window to select recipients 
      from (Intranet Users, Business Directory & Personal Contacts) to send to.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Enter the message's <em>Subject.</em></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Type messages inside the <em>Message 
      Body</em>. By default the compose <em>Message Body</em> is in HTML mode 
      inside a richtext editor.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">4.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Add/Remove Attachments</strong> 
      to attach files. A small window to upload files will appear with a maximum 
      of 3 files per upload.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">5.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">By default, a copy of all messages 
      sent will be saved under the <em>Sent</em> folder. Remove the tick at <em>Copy 
      To Sent</em> if you do not wish to save the message.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">6.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Finally, click on the <strong>Send</strong> 
      button to send out messages or the<strong> Save As Draft</strong> button 
      to save the messages under the <em>Draft</em> folder.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
